Greta Gerwig’s new adaptation of Little Women has struck a resounding chord with audiences, particularly young women.
Louisa May Alcott’s novel Little Women stands out for its frequent revivals, with numerous film and stage adaptations, and has been continuously in print since its first publication.
Little Women is not a feminist guide to action.
The Alcott family home was a station on the Underground Railroad.
Alcott’s work brings focus not only to the historical struggles of women, but to the specific struggles of women artists and authors.